## Summary

Two related bugs cause stale state when navigating between sessions, discovered via E2E testing in coding-tool.

## Origin

Bug fixes from coding-tool commits c355233, 78067cb. Port up to: 78067cb.

## Bug 1: useRealtimeSession stale state

When navigating between sessions, the hook only resets `initialLoadRef`, allowing stale session/students/featured data to briefly appear.

**File:** `frontend/src/hooks/useRealtimeSession.ts` (~line 123)
**Test:** `frontend/src/hooks/__tests__/useRealtimeSession.test.ts`

**Implementation:**
1. Add `const lastSessionIdRef = useRef<string | undefined>(undefined)`
2. At the top of the loadState effect (before the early return), add:
```typescript
if (session_id \!== lastSessionIdRef.current) {
  initialLoadRef.current = false;
  lastSessionIdRef.current = session_id;
  pendingCodeUpdatesRef.current.clear();
  setSession(null);
  setStudents(new Map());
  setFeaturedStudent({});
  setReplacementInfo(null);
  setLoading(true);
  setError(null);
}
```
3. Remove the separate useEffect that only resets `initialLoadRef` (lines 188-191)
4. Add test: navigating to a new session_id clears all state before loading

## Bug 2: Student page stale state on 'Join New Session'

When a student clicks 'Join New Session' after a session replacement, the old session's `sessionEnded`, `joined`, and `joinAttemptedRef` state bleeds into the new session.

**File:** `frontend/src/app/(fullscreen)/student/page.tsx` (after the session status detection effect)

**Implementation:**
Add a reset effect:
```typescript
const prevSessionIdRef = useRef<string | undefined>(sessionIdFromUrl);
useEffect(() => {
  if (sessionIdFromUrl \!== prevSessionIdRef.current) {
    setSessionEnded(false);
    setJoined(false);
    joinAttemptedRef.current = null;
    prevSessionIdRef.current = sessionIdFromUrl;
  }
}, [sessionIdFromUrl]);
```

## Reference

coding-tool commits: c355233, 78067cb

## Summary

Port the session-lifecycle E2E test from coding-tool that covers the instructor's day-to-day workflow end-to-end.

## Origin

coding-tool commit 78067cb. Port up to: 78067cb.

## Test coverage

The test exercises: start session from problem page → student joins → student types code → instructor verifies → instructor starts replacement session → student sees notification → student joins new session → student types in new session → instructor ends session → student runs code in practice mode.

## Files

- `frontend/e2e/session-lifecycle.spec.ts` (new)
- `frontend/e2e/fixtures/api-setup.ts` (add `createProblem` helper)

## Implementation

1. Add `createProblem` to `api-setup.ts`:
```typescript
export async function createProblem(token: string, classId: string, opts: {
  title: string; starterCode?: string; description?: string;
}): Promise<any> {
  const res = await apiFetch('/api/v1/problems', token, {
    method: 'POST',
    body: JSON.stringify({
      title: opts.title,
      class_id: classId,
      starter_code: opts.starterCode || '# Write your solution\n',
      description: opts.description || '',
    }),
  });
  if (res.status \!== 201) throw new Error('Failed to create problem: ' + res.status);
  return res.json();
}
```

2. Port `session-lifecycle.spec.ts` adapting:
   - Use `test` from `./fixtures/test-fixture` (provides `testNamespace`, `setupInstructor`, `logCollector`)
   - Use `signInAs` from `./fixtures/auth` instead of `loginAsInstructor`/`loginAsStudent`
   - Use `registerStudent` from `./fixtures/api-setup`
   - Use `createProblem` (new helper above)
   - Check URL param convention: eval uses `session_id` in some places, `sessionId` in others - match existing E2E tests

## Dependencies

Depends on practice mode being implemented (the final test step runs code in an ended session).

